class Solution {
public:
    int longestSemiRepetitiveSubstring(string s) {
        int n = s.size();
        int maxLen = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
            int count = 0;
            for (int j = i; j < n; ++j) {
                if (j > i && s[j] == s[j - 1]) ++count;
                if (count > 1) break;
                maxLen = max(maxLen, j - i + 1);
            }
        }
        return maxLen;
    }
};
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n^2)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution uses a nested loop to check all substrings of the input string, counting the number of adjacent same digit pairs. It keeps track of the maximum length of a semi-repetitive substring seen so far.
